8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 144, L.D. 221, “An Act to Address the
10 Effect of Changes to Federal Income Tax Laws on Maine Income Tax Laws”
11 Amend the bill in section 2 in §5295 by striking out all of subsection 3 (page 1, lines
12 39 to 44 and page 2, lines 1 and 2 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
13 '3. Notice. Immediately upon making a determination pursuant to subsection 2, the
14 Governor shall notify the President of the Senate, the Speaker of the House of
15 Representatives, the majority and minority leaders of the Senate and House of
16 Representatives, the members of the joint standing committee of the Legislature having
17 jurisdiction over taxation matters and the chairs of the joint standing committee of the
18 Legislature having jurisdiction over appropriations and financial affairs of the specific
19 direction provided to the assessor and the effect of that determination on Maine income tax
20 laws and the state budget.
21 Upon receipt of notice pursuant to this subsection, the joint standing committee of the
22 Legislature having jurisdiction over taxation matters may convene to consider action taken
23 under this section. A hearing held under this section must be held with public notice
24 provided at least 2 full weeks prior to the day of the hearing. The joint standing committee
25 may report out a bill related to the report to the session of the Legislature to which the
26 report is submitted or, if the Legislature is not in session, to the next regular or special
27 session of the Legislature occurring after submission of the report.'
28 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
29 number to read consecutively.
30 SUMMARY
3311 This amendment establishes an additional notice requirement to the joint standing
3322 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over taxation matters. The amendment
3333 authorizes the committee to convene to respond to a determination by the Governor to take
3344 action to address federal income tax law changes. Hearings of the committee are open
